Enumeration Type Documentation

enum eARCOMMANDS_DECODER_ERROR

Error codes for ARCOMMANDS_Decoder_DecodeBuffer function.

Enumerator
ARCOMMANDS_DECODER_OK 

No error occured.

ARCOMMANDS_DECODER_ERROR_NO_CALLBACK 

No error, but no callback was set (so the call had no effect)

ARCOMMANDS_DECODER_ERROR_UNKNOWN_COMMAND 

The command buffer contained an unknown command.

ARCOMMANDS_DECODER_ERROR_NOT_ENOUGH_DATA 

The command buffer did not contain enough data for the specified command.

ARCOMMANDS_DECODER_ERROR_NOT_ENOUGH_SPACE 

The string buffer was not big enough for the command description.

ARCOMMANDS_DECODER_ERROR 

Any other error.

Function Documentation

eARCOMMANDS_DECODER_ERROR ARCOMMANDS_Decoder_DecodeBuffer ( const uint8_t *  buffer,
int32_t  buffLen 
)

Decode a comand buffer On success, the callback set for the command will be called in the current thread.

Parameters
bufferthe command buffer to decode
buffLenthe length of the command buffer
Returns
ARCOMMANDS_DECODER_OK on success, any error code otherwise

ARCOMMANDS_Decoder_t* ARCOMMANDS_Decoder_NewDecoder ( eARCOMMANDS_DECODER_ERROR *  error)

Creates a new ARCOMMANDS_Decoder_t.

Warning
This function allocates memory.
Note
The memory must be freed by a call to ARCOMMANDS_Decoder_DeleteDecoder.
Returns
A new ARCOMMANDS_Decoder_t instance. NULL in case of error.
